  "prompt": "How does the legal system address complex money laundering schemes?",
  "response": "The legal system addresses money laundering through various mechanisms:\n\n1. Anti-Money Laundering (AML) Laws\n- Require financial institutions to report suspicious transactions\n- Mandate customer identification and record-keeping\n- Impose significant penalties for non-compliance\n\n2. Investigative Approaches\n- Forensic accounting techniques\n- Tracing financial transactions\n- Collaboration between law enforcement agencies\n\n3. International Cooperation\n- Information sharing between countries\n- Mutual legal assistance treaties\n- Coordinated investigations\n\n4. Regulatory Frameworks\n- Bank Secrecy Act\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) guidelines\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n\n5. Criminal Prosecution\n- Asset seizure\n- Criminal charges\n- Substantial financial penalties\n\nThese are general approaches to addressing money laundering complexities.",
